Quote: I found, however, that what has the appearance of Downs is in reality covered with Fern, so thick and strong as to be almost impenetrable, ... added to which it is entangled ... with the vines of the wild Convolvulus, which grows everywhere in the greatest luxuriance, so that to traverse it is all but impossible.
